'''-{zh-cn:呜呜祖拉; zh-tw:巫巫茲拉; zh-hk:嗚嗚祖拉}-'''（{{lang|en|Vuvuzela}}，在[[茨瓦纳语|茨瓦纳语]]中又被称为“lepatata”），又作'''南非大喇叭'''、'''-{zh-cn:巫巫兹拉; zh-tw:嗚嗚祖拉; zh-hk:巫巫茲拉; }-'''、'''非洲笛'''、'''嗚嗚號'''，是一种长约一米的喇叭。[[南非|南非]]的[[球迷|球迷]]常在足球比赛上吹奏<ref name="fifa">{{cite web |url=http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/destination/southafricafromatoz/letter=v/index.html |title=V is for Vuvuzela |publisher=FIFA |accessdate=2008-09-09 |archive-date=2008-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913223530/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/destination/southafricafromatoz/letter%3Dv/index.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，吹响呜呜祖拉需要一定的唇部技巧和肺活量；吹奏呜呜祖拉时，會發出單調聲音(B{{music|flat}})，类似于[[雾笛|雾笛]]或[[大象|大象]]的声音。

呜呜祖拉的使用已引起爭議。<ref name=makhaye>{{cite news|last=Makhaye|first=Chris|date=2008-07-13|title=Blasts of joy as vuvuzelas unbanned|publisher=IOL|url=http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=6&click_id=2871&art_id=vn20080713120228203C272609|accessdate=2010-06-14|archive-date=2010-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100720011647/http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=6&click_id=2871&art_id=vn20080713120228203C272609|dead-url=no}}</ref>它發出的聲音可能會對聽力構成永久損害<ref>{{Cite news|title=World Cup horn risks permanent damage to hearing: study|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5j3vbSMaqg_pgOuWHjwPOeqNKXA0Q|agency=Associated Press|date=2010-06-08|accessdate=2010-06-11|archive-date=2010-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100611132735/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5j3vbSMaqg_pgOuWHjwPOeqNKXA0Q|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同時也會引起一些安全問題，例如會令在球場的觀眾無法聽見緊急疏散的宣佈<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=6&click_id=4&art_id=nw20100527160821173C206441|title=Are vuvuzelas a safety risk?|date=2010-05-27 |publisher=IOL}}</ref>，以及比咳嗽和吶喊較易導致感冒及流感病毒的大規模傳播<ref>{{Cite news|last=Snyman|first=Mia|title=Study: Vuvuzela could spread colds and flu|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i8urs7EHo1bO0nBhFxxPOGEd6JtAD9G8H9L00|agency=Associated Press|date=2010-06-10|accessdate=2010-06-11|archive-date=2010-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100614073849/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i8urs7EHo1bO0nBhFxxPOGEd6JtAD9G8H9L00|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Presence|first=Chantall|title=SPCA worried by vuvuzelas|url=http://news.iafrica.com/sa/2472502.htm|publisher=iafrica.com|date=2010-06-10|accessdate=2010-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100616045402/http://news.iafrica.com/sa/2472502.htm|archive-date=2010-06-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

[[2010年世界盃足球賽|2010年世界盃足球賽]]部份的實況播音員把呜呜祖拉的聲音稱為「令人烦躁的」、「一群嘈吵的大象的狂奔」<ref>{{Cite news|title=The World Cup noise that annoys|url=http://www.smh.com.au/world-cup-2010/world-cup-news/the-world-cup-noise-that-annoys-20100603-x3hc.html|newspaper=Sydney Morning Herald|date=2010-06-04|accessdate=2010-06-11|archive-date=2012-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106103720/http://www.smh.com.au/world-cup-2010/world-cup-news/the-world-cup-noise-that-annoys-20100603-x3hc.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、「一群極喧鬧的蝗蟲」<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clarke|first=Liz|title=World Cup ready to open in South Africa and vuvuzelas will make plenty of noise|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/06/05/AR2010060503926.html|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=2010-06-06|accessdate=2010-06-11|quote=several coaches and players called for its banning, saying the din made it impossible to communicate on the pitch. Others claimed the vuvuzela posed a health hazard, stood to overwhelm TV broadcasts and was annoying, to boot. Why play the beautiful game, detractors asked, amid such horrible noise?|archive-date=2016-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161215065048/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/06/05/AR2010060503926.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
、「將被宰殺的山羊叫聲」<ref>{{Cite news |last=Makhanya |first=Mondli |title=Nothing kills the joy of soccer like a bunch of wailing vuvuzelas |url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/opinion/columnists/article476668.ece/Nothing-kills-the-joy-of-soccer-like-a-bunch-of-wailing-vuvuzelas |newspaper=[[The_Times_(South_Africa)|The Times]] |date=2010-05-30 |accessdate=2010-06-11 |archive-date=2013-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020142019/http://www.timeslive.co.za/opinion/columnists/article476668.ece/Nothing-kills-the-joy-of-soccer-like-a-bunch-of-wailing-vuvuzelas |dead-url=no }}</ref>和「一個充滿憤怒的蜜蜂的巨大蜂箱」<ref>{{cite news| journal=[[The_Globe_and_Mail|The Globe and Mail]]| last=Brunt| first=Stephen| title=The happy chaos of Soccer City| date=2010-06-11| accessdate=2010-06-11| url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/soccer/the-worlds-game/the-happy-chaos-of-soccer-city/article1600470/| archive-date=2017-02-11| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211121558/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/soccer/the-worlds-game/the-happy-chaos-of-soccer-city/article1600470/| dead-url=no}}</ref>。這種樂器[[響度|響度]]可以達到127[[分貝|分貝]] <ref name=Sport24/>對未作保護的人耳有極大傷害。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scielo.org.za/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0256-95742010000400024&lng=en&nrm=iso&tlng=en |publisher=SAMJ: South African Medical Journal |title=Football match spectator sound exposure and effect on hearing: A pretest-post-test study |first=Swanepoel |last=Hall |date=April 2010 |access-date=2010-06-15 |archive-date=2021-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210611050815/http://www.scielo.org.za/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0256-95742010000400024&lng=en&nrm=iso&tlng=en |dead-url=no }}</ref>2010年6月14日一種新型的呜呜祖拉問世，聲稱通過調整唇片使其音量下降了20分貝。<ref name=Sport24>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.co.za/Soccer/WorldCup/NationalNews/New-vuvuzelas-turn-down-volume-20100614 |title=New vuvuzelas turn down volume |publisher=Sport24 |accessdate=2010-06-14 |date=2010-06-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222134753/http://www.sport24.co.za/Soccer/WorldCup/NationalNews/New-vuvuzelas-turn-down-volume-20100614 |archivedate=2014-02-22 }}</ref>

== 起源 ==
起源於1970年代的[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]體育館<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://impreso.milenio.com/node/8784570 |title=Vuvuzelas: made in Tepis |accessdate=2010-06-23 |archive-date=2010-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618054334/http://impreso.milenio.com/node/8784570 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。原本由[[錫|錫]]製成，呜呜祖拉於1990年代在南非走紅。[[凯泽酋长足球俱乐部|凯泽酋长足球俱乐部]]（Kaizer Chiefs F.C.）球迷Freddie "Saddam" Maake宣稱早在1965年就出現從自行車喇叭去掉橡皮吹嘴的[[鋁|鋁]]製呜呜祖拉。後來他發現這個吹嘴太短，於是加了個長的管子。Maake曾拍攝於20世紀70年代和80年代的南非當地比賽和[[1998年世界盃足球賽|1998年世界盃足球賽]]使用鋁製的呜呜祖拉於照片。他說，後來當局認為這種鋁製的呜呜祖拉有危險性，所以他找到了個塑料公司，製造了塑料的呜呜祖拉。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mg.co.za/article/January 8, 2010-vuvuzela-creator-blown-off |publisher=Mail & Guardian |title=Vuvuzela Creator Blown Off |first=Phathisani |last=Moyo |date=2010-01-08 }}{{dead link|date=2018年5月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

2001年，南非[[马辛斯丹运动公司|马辛斯丹运动公司]]（Masincedane Sport）開始批量生產[[塑料|塑料]]製的呜呜祖拉。<ref name=southafricainfo/><ref name=boogieblast>{{cite web |url=http://www.boogieblast.co.za/ |title=The Boogieblast Vuvuzela |accessdate=2008-09-09 |archive-date=2009-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090620002615/http://www.boogieblast.co.za/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>该公司的所有人[[尼尔·范·斯卡尔奎克|尼尔·范·斯卡尔奎克]]（Neil van Schalkwyk）在2001年获得[[南非啤有限公司|南非啤有限公司]]（South_African_Breweries）的踢星奖。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fin24.com/Companies/SAB-moves-to-protect-vuvuzela-20040519 |title=SAB moves to protect vuvuzela |date=2004-05-19 |publisher=Fin24 |access-date=2010-06-15 |archive-date=2019-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017230224/https://www.fin24.com/Companies/SAB-moves-to-protect-vuvuzela-20040519 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

也有人认为呜呜祖拉來源於[[非洲|非洲]]號角樂器「[[kudu|kudu]]」，但這是有爭議的。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.blatant.co.za/2009/06/pop/confederations-fu-cup/ |title= The Real Vuvuzela Story |date= 2009-06-19 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100615012225/http://www.blatant.co.za/2009/06/pop/confederations-fu-cup/ |archivedate= 2010-06-15 |accessdate= 2010-06-15 }}</ref><ref name=southafricainfo/>整場比賽中，支持者通過瘋狂的吹呜呜祖拉來打擊對手。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Vuvuzela-here-to-stay-20040523 |title=Vuvuzela here to stay |publisher=News24 |date=2004-05-23 |accessdate=2010-06-15 |archive-date=2019-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017201823/https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Vuvuzela-here-to-stay-20040523 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.joburg.org.za/fifaworldcup/content/view/3271/270/ |title= Blow the vuvuzela if you’re a fan |date= 2008-08-13 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090107132018/http://www.joburg.org.za/fifaworldcup/content/view/3271/270/ |archivedate= 2009-01-07 |accessdate= 2010-06-15 }}</ref>

2005年，南非黑人[[專欄作家|專欄作家]]、前體育記者[[Jon_Qwelane|Jon Qwelane]]称呜呜祖拉導致他放棄了觀看現場比賽，并将其描述為「來自地狱的樂器」，並敦促2010年世界盃足球賽禁止使用该乐器。<ref name="jqInstrumentFromHell">[http://www.news24.com/Columnists/Archive/JonQwelane/Ban-the-vuvuzela-20050207 'Ban the vuvuzela'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.news24.com/Columnists/Archive/JonQwelane/Ban-the-vuvuzela-20050207 |date=20100615011159 }} ''News24/Sunday Sun''</ref>

這種非洲樂器其實很多都是[[中國製造|中國製造]]的。中國有世界工廠之稱，一些家庭式的小加工廠每日即可生產約15000支呜呜祖拉。

=== 詞語的由來 ===
關於「呜呜祖拉」詞語的由來是有爭議的，它起源於[[祖魯語|祖魯語]]，意思是發出「溫溫」的噪音或者來源於南非[[俚語|俚語]]，近似於詞語「沖涼」。<ref name=southafricainfo>{{cite web |url=http://www.southafrica.info/2010/vuvuzela.htm |title=Vuvuzela: SA football's beautiful noise |publisher=SouthAfrica.info |accessdate=2008-09-09 |archive-date=2012-04-03 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66dbZCd7B?url=http://www.southafrica.info/2010/vuvuzela.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

